AGI - Seven members of the Guard Corps of the Iranian Revolution, two commanders and five officers, are lost in the attack attributed to Israel against the Iranian consulate in Damascus. To confirm it are the same "Pasdaran" that, according to the New York Times, were meeting some members of the Palestinian Islamic Jihad.
&nbsp;
According to the Syrian Observatory for Human Rights, an NGO based in London and a network of local collaborators, the attack killed Mohammad Reza Zahedi and Mohammad Hadi Haji Rahimi, respectively commander of the Quds Force of the Iranian revolutionary Guards in Syria and Lebanon, and his deputy, along with the director of his office and two advisers. The observatory had provided a budget of eight victims.
&nbsp;
Hossein Akbari>, Iranian ambassador to Syria, came out unharmed by the attack. An anonymous military source told the Syrian official press agency Sana that the attack of the "Israeli enemy" at the building of the Iranian consulate in Damascus "has completely destroyed the building and hit everyone inside", causing "mothers and wounded" within the consulate, without providing further details.
<h2>Teheran: we will respond hard
Akbari assured that Tehran will respond "duringly" to Israel for the attack, which he claims to have witnessed from the window of his residence. According to the diplomat, the consulate was attacked by six missiles launched by F-35 aircraft. "The Zionist regime (Israel) is acting against international law, so it will receive a harsh response from us," Akbari said on Iranian television, in connection with Damascus.
&nbsp;
Iranian Foreign Minister invited "the international community" to provide "a serious response" to the raid. During a phone call with his Syrian counterpart, Iranian Foreign Minister Hossein Amir-Abdollahian>&nbsp;" he argued that the attack on an annex of the Iranian embassy in Damascus is a violation of all international obligations and conventions, blamed the Zionist regime for the consequences of this action and stressed the need for a serious response from the international community to such criminal actions.
<div </div
<h2>"Made condemnation of Moscow
The Russian government accused Israel of carrying out an "unacceptable" attack against an Iranian diplomatic headquarters in Syria. "We firmly condemn this unacceptable attack against the Iranian consular mission in Syria," said the Foreign Ministry in a statement.
&nbsp;
"We call on the Israeli leadership to stop the provocative acts of armed violence against the territory of Syria and neighbouring countries," the ministry concluded, warning of the risk of "extremely dangerous consequences" for the region.
<h2> For Nyt the goal was a meeting between Pasdaran and Islamic Jihad</h2>
The attack on the Iranian consulate in Damascus aimed at a "secret meeting" between senior Iranian intelligence officials, the Al-Quds Force, and Islamic Jihad men gathered to discuss the war in Gaza. A source of the Iranian Revolution Guards reported this to the New York Times. According to Israeli sources, the attached building was not a diplomatic office but a headquarters of the 'pasdaran,' therefore a military target.
&nbsp;
In the attack, according to a note spread to Tehran from the same Guards of the Revolution, at least three generals of the Iranian Al-Quds Force were killed, the military and intelligence service of the Guards of the Islamic Revolution, along with four other officers of the Revolutionary Guards. It was one of the most lethal attacks of the underground war between Israel and Iran.&nbsp;
&nbsp;

