AGI - The Conservative Party Akp of Turkish President Recep Tayip Erdogan wakes up this morning after the heaviest defeat of his history, suffered in the administrative elections that yesterday called to the polls 61 million voters throughout Turkey. A result that, on the contrary, was celebrated in the great cities by carcasses and crowds at feast that celebrated the triumph of the opposition, but also the batosta of Erdogan, until late night. The Turkish President is not a politician used to lose and yesterday he has failed heavily to regain Istanbul and Ankara, but he also lost in the other three most populous cities of Turkey getting a much more sound defeat than five years ago. Just think that in the capital Ankara the gap between the outgoing mayor Mansur Yavas and the candidate of Erdogan is almost 30 points, while in Istanbul, torn in 2019 after a fight to the last vote, the opposition leader Ekrem Imamoglu was confirmed mayor with 11 detachments on Murat Kurum. Chosen personally by Erdogan to reconquer the metropolis on the Bosphorus, the latter has proved to be a mediocre character, unable to trace and conquer voters. All the contrary of Imamoglu, a political animal that for months has asserted the results achieved in the previous five years and with pride has responded to the attacks suffered by the judiciary. The defeat of 2019 had left Erdogan the consolation of maintaining control over the majority of districts of the city; 5 years later the Republican People's Party (Chp) completely overturned the situation, from 16 to 26 districts conquered on a total of 39. Among these are the victories of the Chp in the stronghold of Uskudar, where he votes the same Erdogan, but also in the very central Beyoglu, held at the Akp of Erdogan for 30 years.
